A circus has had two dogs confiscated – after police said they were painted black and white to fool customers who expected to see pandas.

Police in Brescia, Italy, seized the chow chows amid claims circus-goers were being tricked into handing over cash just to pose for photos with the animals.

Officers were tipped off about the male and female animals, which were being put on display before the circus show started.

