According to the website Thelocal.it, specialist police officers then swooped and confiscated the dogs which had been painted black and white.

Children had been paying a fee to have their photo taken with the animals - believing them to be pandas, police said. 

The dogs were said to be in a healthy state when they were taken away but had ‘watery eyes’.

