The website quotes a police spokesman as saying that this was ‘probably aggravated by the continuous exposure to camera flashes’.

Officers acted on animal cruelty grounds, and the local reports that the owners are facing charges over the dogs’ false passports.

Police said that the chow chows were brought in from Hungary and may have been six months younger than their documents had suggested.

The 'Orfei' circus involved has today denied the allegations insisting that they never claimed the dogs were pandas.

The circus secretar, Riccardo Gravina reportedly told IBTimes: 'It's obvious they are dogs.

'No animal was mistreated. They are like children to us.'  

